================================================================================
  ARCHITECTURE SUMMARY
================================================================================

SERVICES DESIGNED:
  1. api-gateway        - HTTP entry point, JWT validation, request routing
  2. auth-service       - Staff login, JWT token generation, roles
  3. order-service      - Open bills, items, order lifecycle
  4. payment-service    - Checkout, final totals, payments
  5. promotion-service  - Promotion rules, discount calculation

DATA OWNERSHIP:
  auth-service         ‚Üí owns: users, user_roles
  order-service        ‚Üí owns: orders, order_items
  payment-service      ‚Üí owns: payments, payment_methods, order_discounts
  promotion-service    ‚Üí owns: promotions, promotion_usage

COMMUNICATION:
  REST/HTTP (synchronous calls between services)
  Shared PostgreSQL database

KEY DECISIONS:
  ‚úì Microservices (not monolith)
  ‚úì One PostgreSQL database
  ‚úì REST/HTTP for service calls
  ‚úì JWT authentication
  ‚úì Handler ‚Üí Service ‚Üí Repository pattern
  ‚úì Docker + Kubernetes for deployment
  ‚úì Tilt for local development

